# Docker

## Build an image from a Dockerfile 
`docker build --tag <IMAGE_NAME>:<VERSION> <PATH>`
where <PATH> is the directory containing the Dockerfile

## Add a volume when creating an image
in the Dockerfile, add:
`VOLUME  <VOLUME_PATH>`
where <VOLUME_PATH> is the path to the volume in the container

## Bind a volume to a file when creating a container:
Use docker run (as above) with the additional option:
`-v my_volume:<CONTAINER_PATH>`

# SSH into a container
`docker exec -it <CONTAINER_NAME> /bin/bash`


# Dremio

## backup
<DREMIO_HOME>/bin/dremio-admin backup
    -u <DREMIO_ADMIN_USER> \
    -p <DREMIO_ADMIN_PASS> \
    -d <BACKUP_PATH>

## restore
<DREMIO_HOME>/bin/dremio-admin -r <BACKUP_PATH>


## Create a bare Docker container from the Dremio image
`docker run -p 9047:9047 -p 31010:31010 -p 45678:45678 dremio/dremio-oss`
